details.comment:
Links, locate, logcat, logger: Utilities for interacting with system files and commands.
login, look: Commands to access user authentication or search directories respectively.
losetup, lscpu, lsipc, lsof, ltrace: Various utilities to interact with the kernel and file systems.
lzmadec, lzmainfo: Utilities for working with LZMA compressed files.
make, mandoc, mcookie: Build and documentation generation tools.
meson: A modern build system for multiple platforms and languages.
mii-tool, mkfs, mkfs.bfs, etc: File system management utilities.
mount, mpicalc: Utilities for mounting and basic calculations.
msgattrib, msgcat, msgcmp, etc: Text processing and conversion tools.
namei, nameif: Tools to display information about files and network interfaces.
nano: A simple text editor for quick edits.
netstat, ngettext: Network status and internationalization utilities.
objcopy, objdump: Utilities to manipulate object code (binary) files.
proot, prove: Tools for running processes in a chrooted environment or testing Perl modules respectively.
prlimit, procs: Resource management tools.
pydoc2.7, pydoc3.8: Documentation generation tools for Python 2.7 and 3.8 respectively.
python2.7, python3.8, python2.7-config, python3.8-config: Tools to interact with the respective versions of Python.
